FT  07 NOV 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pepper prices have remained steady after the recent uptrend, reports
Man-producten. Some origins, including Indonesia and India, reduced their
prices slightly and this made buyers more cautious. Brazil - normally the
main supplier at this time of year - reports that the crop might be halved
from last year's level. White pepper is offered at Dollars 1,550 a tonne cif
and only slightly lower on shipment basis. Black pepper is available at
Dollars 1,350 to Dollars 1,400 spot and at Dollars 1,250 to Dollars 1,350
cif on shipment basis.
