<HEADLINE>
FT  07 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Arthur Shaw makes inroads into losses
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ARTHUR SHAW, which serves the building industry, continued in loss for the
half year ended October 4, albeit at a considerably reduced rate, and is
passing the interim dividend.
After exceptional charges, the pre-tax loss was Pounds 124,000 compared with
a deficit of Pounds 523,000 in the preceding six months and a profit of
Pounds 113,000 in the opening half of 1991.
Losses per share came to 1.03p. Earnings last time were 0.86p and an interim
dividend of 1.3p was paid - but no final.
Mr Gordon Pearson, chairman, said the cost savings that had been made fell
predominantly in the second half.
Turnover in the half year was Pounds 8.05m (Pounds 7.79m) and the operating
profit came to Pounds 99,000 (Pounds 202,000).
