<HEADLINE>
FT  07 NOV 92 / London ambulance inquiry ordered
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN INQUIRY into manage-ent, computer operations and industrial relations at
the London Ambulance Service was ordered yesterday by Mrs Virginia
Bottomley, health secretary. It will last three months and be led by Mr Don
Page, chief executive of the South Yorkshire Ambulance Service.
The inquiry, the report from which will be published, is intended to restore
public confidence following the breakdown of the computerised emergency 999
call system. It has been claimed that recent computer failures led to the
deaths of some patients.
Mrs Bottomley said in the Commons there was a need to 'identify the lessons
to be learned'.
