FT  06 NOV 92 / International Company News: Hungary alters view on BZW
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NICHOLAS DENTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUDAPEST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Hungarian authorities yesterday withdrew their criticism of Barclays de
Zoete Wedd, the UK merchant bank which was sacked on Wednesday as adviser on
the privatisation of Kobanyai Sorgyar, Hungary's largest brewery.
The State Property Agency's managing director, Mr Lajos Csepi, yesterday met
Mr Charles Kovacs, head of BZW's Hungarian office. Afterwards, the SPA
issued a statement that 'due to miscommunication, the true intention of the
SPA board was not clearly communicated to BZW which led to steps taken by
BZW which were found objectionable by the SPA'.
BZW had sent out prospectuses for Kobanyai to international brewers, which
the Hungarian authorities wanted excluded for competition reasons.
</TEXT>
