<TEXT>
Philip Rawstorne ('OFT is promised pub checklist', November 3) is incorrect
when he states that regional brewers Boddingtons and Devenish have closed
their breweries. The Boddingtons brewery was sold to Whitbread, since when
it has never been busier. And Devenish's Redruth brewery was bought by its
management and now produces beer both for the local pub trade and the
national take-home business.
Rawstorne is correct to point out that beer prices in pubs have continued to
rise faster than inflation and that the major brewers' grip on the UK beer
market has increased. The long-term supply agreements negotiated by the
major brewers with many of the new pub companies need Office of Fair Trading
investigation. Iain R Loe,
research manager,
Campaign for Real Ale,
