<HEADLINE>
FT  06 NOV 92 / Letter: Competition essential
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr F BIZZARI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A practice is developing among the water, electricity, telecommunications
and gas companies which is having a significant effect on the construction
and engineering consultancy services in the UK.
These monopolies are buying small and medium-size contractors and
consultancies and are carrying out an ever-increasing proportion of such
work in-house. This is inefficient and the effects of it are passed on to
the consumer, undetected by the watchdogs.
I believe the utilities should be prohibited from acting as contractors and
consultants for engineering services needed in the upgrading, modernisation
and installation of their facilities. They should rely on a clear, defined
procedure of open market competition. F Bizzari,
managing director,
Lilley International,
PO Box 5242,
Dubai,
United Arab Emirates
</TEXT>
