FT  06 NOV 92 / Technology: Orange solvent in green crusade - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An alternative to going 'green' is to go orange. This is the approach at
Total Oil Great Britain which has launched a multi-purpose solvent cleaner
made from oranges.
Called Natural Degreaser, the product is formulated from a blend of
highly-refined mineral oils and orange oils, and has been developed to
replace chlorinated- and paraffin-based cleaners in a variety of industrial
and commercial applications.
Total says the product will safely remove everything oil-based - from
creosote to chewing gum - in a way which will minimise damage to the
environment since it is non-toxic. Where recovery is possible, the product
is 90 per cent reusable by volume if filtered. Total Oil Great Britain: UK,
0977 673421.
