FT  06 NOV 92 / Battery maker reviews staffing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EVER READY, the battery manufacturer, is to cut 175 jobs at its Newburn
plant, Newcastle upon Tyne, as part of a review of its European operations
by Ralston Purina, its US parent.
The cuts follow a decision to end production of alkaline batteries at
Newburn. A staff of 30 will remain to continue producing zinc-carbon
batteries. The Newburn factory will operate as a satellite of the company's
other plant at Tanfield Lea, County Durham.
Ever Ready, which was acquired by the consumer-products conglomerate in
July, said the single European market meant battery companies operating
single, large-scale manufacturing plants would increasingly have a
competitive cost advantage over those with small factories serving
individual countries.
