</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
JP MORGAN yesterday launched the first issue of warrants on an emerging
markets bond index - a further step towards emerging market derivative
products. Warrants on equity indices, American depository receipts, foreign
bonds and local debt instruments are among the derivative products sold to
investors.
The issue consists of up to 250,000 one-year call warrants, worth about
Dollars 60m, on the JP Morgan Emerging Markets Bond Index. They will be
cash-settled.
The index was introduced this year to track benchmark dollar-denominated
bonds issued as part of the restructuring of countries' external bank debt.
The index includes debt totalling Dollars 43bn issued by Mexico, Venezuela,
Brazil, the Philippines and Nigeria.
