FT  06 NOV 92 / International Company News: Du Pont stops fungicide payment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DU PONT, the leading US chemicals group, said yesterday it would stop making
payments to horticultural growers who claimed its Benlate DF fungicide had
damaged their crops.
The company, which last year took a Dollars 215m after-tax charge because of
such claims, said yesterday it had paid more than Dollars 470m in claims
from ornamental plant and fruit growers since Benlate was withdrawn from the
market in 1991.
Du Pont claimed yesterday that its own studies showed the Benlate fungicide
did not cause the crop damage. Based on these findings, the company said it
would no longer pay any claims.
The company said it had initially begun paying Benlate-related claims
because its scientists believed at the time there was a high probability
that the fungicide would eventually be shown to have contributed to plant
damage.
